<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT March 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian security head Jibril Rajoub denied
Monday Israel's accusations that the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) had given green-light to terrorist attacks and
even organized riots.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- U.S. Vice President Al Gore arrived in Beijing from
Tokyo Monday evening on a five-day official visit to China at the
invitation of Chinese Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- A strong explosion rocked a branch office of the
Dresdner Bank in western Germany early Monday morning, causing
extensive property damage. But there were no immediate reports of
injury.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy Monday called
on Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, currently abroad, to return
home to intervene personally in the current crisis.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- United States Vice President Al Gore, together with
Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto, Monday ruled out the
possibility of any cutbacks in U.S. military presence in Japan and
the rest of Asia.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia and China will sign important political and
economic agreements at the Sino-Russian summit scheduled for next
month, Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Grigory Karasin said here
today. 
</P>
