<HEADLINE> Access to Refugees in Zaire a Problem: UNHCR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The biggest problem facing
the office of the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) in
the war-torn Zaire is to get access to people displaced by war
there, a senior U.N. official said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Cape Town, UNHCR Chief Sadako Ogato
said: "We are talking to the allies to let us do our work,
especially at the Lubumbo Refugee Camp."
</P>
<P>
Efforts to get access to the people caught up in the war would
be intensified as these people need help immediately, said Ogato.
</P>
<P>
Ogato arrived in South Africa for a four-day visit to update
leaders on the refugee crisis in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after her arrival earlier in the day, Ogato held talks
with President Nelson Mandela at his Cape Town official
residence.
</P>
<P>
Ogato is also scheduled to address the parliament on Tuesday
about the refugee crisis and its solutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
