<HEADLINE> British Defense Secretary Meets With Chinese Army Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary Michael
Portillo said today his country is in full readiness to promote
bilateral relations and strengthen cooperation with China,
particularly in the military field.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Fu Quanyou, a member of China's Central
Military Commission and chief of the General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, Portillo said that since both Britain
and China are permanent members of the U.N. Security Council and
play an important role in the world, there should be more reason
that the two countries increase contacts and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
"We not only respect China's past, but also have full
confidence on its future and believe that China will play a very
important role in the world arena," the British defense secretary
said.
</P>
<P>
General Fu, who arrived here Saturday on a five-day official
visit, said China is ready to strhe return of Hong Kong to China, a key issue in

the Sino-British relationship and a great event in the world, Fu
said that as there are only 99 days left before the handover on
June 30, both sides should handle the remaining issues properly
with the spirit of friendliness and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"This is also a test to the bilateral relations between China
and Britain," the Chinese general added.
</P>
<P>
He said that after the transfer of government in Hong Kong, the
Chinese government will hold on to the "one country, two systems"
concept laid out by the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, and
will guarantee the prosperity and development of the Hong Kong
society with the policies of "Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong" and a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Fu also believed that after Hong Kong returns to China, both
countries will keep a good and healthy relationship between them.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in London, Fu will also hold talks with British
Deputy Prime Minister Michael Heseltine and Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Jeremy Hanley and visit British military bases.
</P>
</TEXT>
