<HEADLINE> Fortune Global Forum Opens in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 Fortune Global Forum
opened today as more than 150 international corporate leaders,
statesmen and academics were meeting to focus on the challenges
facing Asia's economic development.
</P>
<P>
With the theme entitled "sustaining the miracle," the
participants will tackle the most urgent problem - whether Asia
can sustain its economic miracle during the past years.
</P>
<P>
The participants, including chairmen, chief executive officers
and presidents of some large multinational corporations, also will
look at the issues that affect the most crucial drivers of growth.
</P>
<P>
Topics to be covered during the business sessions of the forum,
the third one held by Fortune magazine, will range from new global
leadership skills, links between the world economy and capital
markets, relations between business and government, and the future
of the world economy.
</P>
<P>
The event is also co-sponsored by Thailand's Board of
Investments, the Export Promotion Department of the Commerce
Ministry, and the Tourism Authority of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The first Fortune Global Forum was held in Singapore in 1995
and the second was held in Barcelona, Spain last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
