<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Burkina Faso's President Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Burkina Faso's President
Blaise Compaore arrived in Kuwait today for a three-day official
visit for promotion of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Burkina Faso's president, accompanied by his minister of
state for environment and water resources, minister of foreign
affairs and other government officials, will hold talks with the
Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah on means to enhance
the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the second visit by the African leader to the Arab
oil-rich emirate since 1992. Blaise made his first tour to the
country in December 1992.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in 1993, Burkina Faso's Minister of Finance and
Planning Rock Marc Christian Kabore visited Kuwait during which
he praised the Kuwaiti role in funding African projects through
the Kuwaiti Fund for Arab Economic Development.
</P>
<P>
The Fund started operation in Burkina Faso in 1983 by
financing projects in the fields of agriculture, water and weirs
with an accumulated fund of nearly 45 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
