<HEADLINE> Arafat Offers to Help End Conflict in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colombo, March 24 (Xinhua) -- President of the Palestinian
National Authority Yassar Arafat offered to help negotiate a
settlement between the Sri Lankan government and Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
He said that he wholeheartedly supported President Chandrika
Kumaratunga's efforts to reestablish peace in the island country.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who arrived in Colombo today on a two-day official
visit, delivered a special address at a public meeting here
tonight.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was organized by the Foreign Ministry in
association with the Sri Lankan Committee for Solidarity with
Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said that he cannot forget the support of Sri Lanka for
the Palestinian cause.
</P>
<P>
He said that this was his first visit to Sri Lanka and he hoped
that peace would be achieved in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said in response to a question that he was willing to offer
his services to the resolution of the north-east conflict in Sri
Lanka.
</P>
</TEXT>
