<HEADLINE> Equatorial Guinea's Opposition Party to End Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The delegation of the Social
Democratic Coalition of Equatorial Guinea, an opposition party
founded seven years ago, will end its visit to Mozambique next
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by the party's chairman Santiago Obama,
arrived at Mozambique Friday at the invitation of Mozambique's
ruling party Mozambique Liberation Front (FRELIMO).
</P>
<P>
Obama was quoted by Mozambican Information Agency as saying
here today that FRELIMO may associate his party's political
activities while his party will try to keep constant contacts
with FRELIMO.
</P>
<P>
Obama himself has held talks with FRELIMO's chief Manuel Tome
over these issues.
</P>
<P>
FRELIMO, set up in 1962, has rich experiences and enjoys a
high international fame. It is believable and can be an example
for many African parties for it has done a lot since the
anti-colonization era, Obama praised.
</P>
<P>
He added there are a lot of things for his party, which
started to develop relations with FRELIMO three years ago, to
learn from FRELIMO as a part of its preparation for joining
Equatorial Guinea's forthcoming elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
