<HEADLINE> Palestine Accuses Israel of Using Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Minister for Higher Education of
the Palestinian National Authority Hanan Ashrawi said here today
that Israel was exploiting the peace process to confiscate more
Palestinian land and to build and expand settlements.
</P>
<P>
"The peace process has become a unilateral process of power
politics which Israel exploits to confiscate more Palestinian
land, to build and expand settlements, to consolidate its illegal
annexation of occupied Jerusalem and to complete the siege and
isolation of the city," Ashrawi said.
</P>
<P>
She was speaking at the 53rd session of the United Nations
Commission on Human Rights. She was at last allowed to speak at
the session as an honored guest after a long discussion on whether
she could speak from the podium in the hall.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinian-Israeli peace process is in serious jeopardy,
violence is unleashed on our world claiming the lives of innocents
on both sides, the extremism of the Israeli government is feeding
extremist elements among us, and the peace partnership which we
have so painfully and painstakingly sought to build is now being
dissolved in favor of a relationship of occupier-occupied,"
Ashrawi said.
</P>
<P>
Ashrawi said that Israel was unilaterally preempting the
outcome of permanent status issues and flagrantly reneging on the
Interim Phase agreements by continuing to hold hostage more than
3,000 Palestinian prisoners.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the session today, an Israeli representative said
that what was accused by Ashrawi of having been happening "simply
does not exist." "Palestinians have never given up terror," the
representative claimed, adding that peace could only be reached by
talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
