<HEADLINE> Meeting of Communist Parties from Middle East Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A two-day conference attended by
delegations of communist and labor parties from Middle East
countries ended here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, attended by delegations from Egypt, Iran,
Israel, Jordan, Cyprus, Bahrein, Palestine, Syria and the Sudan,
made a joint assessment of the situation in the eastern
Mediterranean and Balkans regions, especially the recent
developments in Albania as well the stance of the Israelis and
