<HEADLINE> 120 Tons of Sugar Stolen from Factory in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- As many as 120 tons of sugar
has been taken out of the Metehare Sugar Factory, some 180
kilometers away from Addis Ababa, by a man under false name and
with a forged document.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency today quoted the factory's General
Manager Belete Alemayehu as saying that the man's identity has
not been established so far.
</P>
<P>
He said the loss was discovered by the finance officials of
the factory when examining the sales and revenue accounts of the
past two years.
</P>
<P>
"One of our employees working in the warehouse has been
detained after a document indicating the sugar was taken out
illegally in March 1995 was found," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
