<HEADLINE> UNHCR Donates Water Containers, Pumps to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A donation of water
containers, pumps, sterilizing agents and vehicles from the U.N.
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) has reached here today for
refugees in eastern Ethiopia facing chronic water scarcity.
</P>
<P>
According to the UNHCR representative here, the donation,
worth 500,000 U.S. Dollars, includes 135 canvas, plastic
containers capable of holding over 200,000 liters of water, three
vehicles, pumps and sterilizing chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The donation will be transported to three camps in Jijiga
within the coming three days.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR has collected the donation from European countries who
are in response to the call for emergency aid to the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
