<HEADLINE> Hillary Clinton Arrives in Tanzania for Private </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States of
America First Lady, Mrs Hillary Clinton arrived in Dar es Sallaam
today for a private visit to Tanzania as fourth leg of her
African tour.
</P>
<P>
Mrs Clinton was met at the Dar es Salaam International Airport
by her Tanzanian counterpart, Mama Anna Mkapa and USA ambassdor
to Tanzania, Bredy Anderson.
</P>
<P>
According to a report, she also met President Benjamin Mkapa
at the State House in the city today before attending women's
round table at the National Museum also in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
At the ruond table, Mrs Clinton was told by participants that
poverty, rural development, education and repproductive health
mostly affected women's advancement.
</P>
<P>
They told Mrs. Clinton that despite vast economic potentials
Tanzania has, financial and technical supports were urgently
needed to help women "take off" in various ventures.
</P>
<P>
Responding, Mrs. Clinton said her country would continue
assisting Tanzania in her efforts to curb various social and
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
She also hailed Tanzania for sustaining peace and stability.
On economic reforms, Mrs clinton said, "your contry is under
right path in the transition period".
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Clinton, who is expected to visit national parks in
Northern Tanzania, has already visited South Africa, Senegal and
Zimbabwe and she is scheduled to go to Uganda and Eritrea. She is
accompanied by her daugther Chelsea during the visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
