<HEADLINE> 128 Alleged Perpetrators of Red Terror Go on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The second criminal bench of
Ethiopia's Federal High Court today began hearing charges filed
against 128 alleged perpetrators of red terror in the late
seventies and the beginning of the eighties.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, among the 128
defendants are the olympic gold medal winner captain Mamo Wolde
and the one time president of the Addis Ababa University
professor Alemayehu Tefera Meshesha.
</P>
<P>
According to charges brought against the individuals, they
were allegedly members of district administration, the
revolutionary campaign coordinating and red terror committees and
have been engaged in aggravated genocide which they carried out
through the anti-revolutionary investigation and commando team
they set up during the stated period. The defendants were accused
of arbitrary detention of alleged members of the Ethiopian
Revolutionary Party, torturing inmates, inflicting untold
suffering and bodily damages including killings.
</P>
<P>
According to Ethiopia's special prosecutors office, it has
charged a total of 5,198 alleged perpetrators of the red terror.
2,246 of them are charged while they are in detention, the
remaining 2,952 were indicted in absentia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
