<HEADLINE> Netherlands to Offer Money to Renovate Schools in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch government will provide
320,000 U.S. Dollars from this year to build or renovate schools
in Hui La, Namibe and Cunene, three once war-torn provinces in
southern Angola, the Angolan News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to restore 10 schools in Hui La, six
schools in Namibe and five schools in Cunene with the number of
restored classrooms reaching 126 and more than 10,000 teachers
and pupils benefitted, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Children Fund will be in charge of the project, which
is planned to be completed in 1998. The fund will also offer aids
on textbooks to the southern African country, said the report.
</P>
<P>
It said the Dutch offer aims mainly to promote the education
capacity in these areas where most of education facilities have
been seriously damaged since the civil war broke out again in
late 1992, causing the dropout of thousands of students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
