<HEADLINE> Defense Secretary Says U.S. Troops Prepared for Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary William
Cohen on Monday said that some 200 U.S. soldiers were on standby
near Zaire to prepare for a possible evacuation of American
citizens and more than 600 troops should be in the area in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
"There has been no request for an evacuation at this time and
we stand at the ready to respond if necessary," Cohen told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
"We've made contingency plans to take care of our citizens
should it be necessary to have an evacuation," Cohen said.
</P>
<P>
Another 1,000 Marines were heading for the region aboard the
helicopter landing ship Nassau, which helped to evacuate Americans
from Albania. Defense officials said it would take the ship about
10 days to arrive in the area.
</P>
<P>
About 650 Americans had been living in Zaire, most of them in
the capital Kinshasa. By Friday, the number was down to about 500,
including 320 in Kinshasa, according to the State Department.
</P>
