<HEADLINE> WFP Allocates 500 Tons of Food to Drought Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 24 (Xinhua) -- World Food Program (WFP)
has allocated 500 tons of food to be distributed immediately to
most drought hit areas in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The Minister for Agriculture and Co-operatives, Paul Kimiti
told reporters here today that according to the WFP arrangement,
the 500 tons, which aimed for Simanjiro, Kiteto, Monduli,
Ngorongoro and Lindi region, will be distributed through
non-governmental organisations (NGOs).
</P>
<P>
The minister attributed to reasons for NGOs to be used in
distributing food as to avoid food misuse and political
ideologies.
</P>
<P>
