<HEADLINE> International Community Sends Relief Aid to DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- International organizations
including the United Nations Development Program (UNDP), have sent
more than 6,500 tons of barley seeds and 800 tons of fertilizer to
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea(DPRK) over the last few
months, the Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The seeds were in time for the first of the country's two
planting seasons, the KCNA said.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP also sent 600,000 U.S. dollars worth of excavators and
bulldozers for the rehabilitation of arable land in North Hwanghae
Province, where farm land was severely damaged by last year's
floods.
</P>
<P>
"This has encouraged the Korean people in their work to repair
flood damage at an early date and brought about a fresh upsurge in
agricultural production," the KCNA said.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK has suffered serious flooding for the past two years
which has devastated agricultural production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
