<HEADLINE> PLA Men Plant Trees to Help Ensure Clean Water Supply for HK People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,300 officers and
men of the People's Liberation Army came to Longbei Hill in
Shenzhen early this morning, to plant trees meant to help conserve
the limpid water supply of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhenwu and Xiong Ziren, commander and political commissar
of the PLA troops stationed in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, attended the voluntary activity.
</P>
<P>
A poster written as "Let the Hong Kong people have the purest
water" was erected on the hillside.
</P>
<P>
An official from Shenzhen city said the Shenzhen reservoir,
built in 1960, is a base of freshwater supply for the six million
people in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Trees planted in the Longbei Hill can not only maintain a good
ecology, but also purify the water source as well as increase the
quality of the water, he added.
</P>
<P>
Commander Liu said to plant trees for water conservation will
be a benefit for future generations, and it is meaningful that the
PLA officers and men can do such a good deed for the people of
Hong Kong before stationed there.
</P>
<P>
The trees planted by the PLA soldiers today are good-quality
fast-growing trees imported from Australia. A tropical rain forest
is expected to form on Longbei Hill just within a couple of
years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
