<HEADLINE> Paintings by Chinese Artists to Be Auctioned in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of oil paintings and
watercolors by contemporary Chinese artists will be auctioned here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The large-scale auction is to be jointly organized by Art House
of Collectors H.K. Ltd., Hong Kong Auctioneers and Estate Agency
Ltd. and the Museum of Chinese Historical Relics.
</P>
<P>
At an opening ceremony of a preview of all the 99 pieces of
art, a spokesman for the organizers said they see good prospects
for Hong Kong's fine arts market and expect the auction to help
enhance links between artists and collectors in China's inland
areas, Hong Kong and beyond.
</P>
<P>
Two oil paintings, titled Nudes and Violin Melodic
respectively, by late Chinese master Xu Beihong, attracted lots of
eyesight.
</P>
<P>
The preview at the Museum of Chinese Historic relics will last
two days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
