<HEADLINE> New World Raises Fund to Finance PCS in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- New World PCS Ltd today signed
a loan agreement with a syndicate of 14 local and international
banks to raise 1.5 billion HK dollars (192.31 million US dollars)
through a credit facility to finance its personal communications
services (PCS) network.
</P>
<P>
Sources from New World said this is the first syndicated
facility to be arranged for a PCS provider in Hong Kong. The
facility has a maturity of up to eight years, but is subject to an
extension option to be exercised by the lenders at the end of the
fifth year.
</P>
<P>
New World PCS, owned jointly by Hong Kong's New World Telephone
Holdings Ltd and a Thai company, was granted a 10-year license to
operate a PCS network by the Hong Kong government in September
1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
