<HEADLINE> HK Auctions Two Land Lots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong sold two land lots
for 13.22 billion HK dollars (1.69 billion US dollars) at a public
auction held by the Lands Department this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The first lot, with an area of about 25,592 sq.m., was sold to
Silver Link Investment Ltd at 11.82 billion HK dollars (1.52
billion US dollars), with bidding opened at 6.3 billion HK
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The second lot was sold to Maxjet Company Ltd at 1.4 billion HK
dollars( 179.49 million US dollars), which has an area of about
2,627 sq.m. The bidding was opened at 800 million HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The first lot is required for non-industrial purposes, while
the second lot is earmarked for private residential purposes.
</P>
