<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Arrives in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paris, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), arrived
here this afternoon for a six-day official visit to France.
</P>
<P>
The first Chinese NPC leader to visit france, Qiao is invited
by President of the Senate Rene Monory and President of the
National Assembly Philippe Seguin.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued at the airport, Qiao said he hopes his
visit will enhance mutual understanding and friendship between
China and France, between the Chinese and French peoples and
between China's NPC and the French parliament, and strengthen
mutually-beneficial cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that France plays an important role in international
affairs and China has attached great importance to developing
friendly relations and cooperation with France.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, he said, the two countries have
witnessed encouraging achievements in the economic, trade,
scientific and technological and cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that the establishment of stable and lasting
relations of friendship and cooperation between China and France,
based on mutual respect and mutual benefit and geared toward the
21st century, not only conforms to the fundamental interests of
the two peoples but is also in the interest of peace, stability
and development in the world.
</P>
<P>
Qiao was greeted at the airport by French National Assembly's
Vice President Gaillard, Chinese Ambassador to France Cai Fangbei
and other senior French officials.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in France, Qiao is expected to meet French
President Jacques Chirac, parliament leaders and other senior
French officials and exchange views with them on the further
development of bilateral ties between China and France, as well as
other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
France is the first leg of his European and Asian tour. He will
also visit Norway, Italy and Mongolia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
