<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Involved in Cash Robbery Executed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A man convicted of armed robbery
of bank vehicles and two of his weapon suppliers were executed
today in Beijing, the Supreme People's Court announced.
</P>
<P>
The death sentence on Guo Song and Zhang Jianguo, two jobless
people from Beijing and northeast China's Heilongjiang Province,
and Nong Zhibao, a farm worker from the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in south China, was carried out this morning by the Beijing
No.1 Intermediate People's Court.
</P>
<P>
Between December 1995 and August 1996, Lu Xianzhou, an escaped
prisoner, aged 33, ganged up with Guo and made four armed
robberies of cash-delivering vehicles of several local banks,
seizing more than 1.8 million RMB yuan, 610,000 Japanese yen,
18,000 US dollars, and 48,000 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
With guns bought from Zhang and Nong, they killed or seriously
wounded 18 guards, and also stole five deluxe sedan cars to
conduct the robberies.
</P>
<P>
Lu was arrested by the police last September and fatally
wounded in resistance. He died in a hospital after confessing the
crimes.
</P>
<P>
According to his confession and other evidence, the Beijing
No.1 Intermediate People's Court sentenced Guo to death and
deprivation of political rights for robbery and theft, and passed
the same penalty on Zhang and Nong for illegally trading guns and
causing extremely serious consequences.
</P>
<P>
The other four men and a woman involved in the case were
convicted of illegal trading of guns, harboring criminals, and
concealing booty. They received punishments ranging from the death
penalty with two-year reprieve and deprivation of political
rights for life to three to seven years in prison.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
