<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Educational Loan to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today announced it will give Indonesia an 85 million US dollar
loan to upgrade its secondary schools.
</P>
<P>
The enrollment rate in senior secondary schools in the country
is expected to increase sharply when educational standards are
upgraded through the loan, the Manila-based ADB said.
</P>
<P>
Senior secondary schools under the Ministry of Religious
Affairs in Indonesia account for about 427,000 students, or 15
percent of the total enrollment, at the secondary level.
</P>
<P>
Raising the quality of senior secondary education on a
sustainable basis will support the Indonesian government's efforts
to increase the gross enrollment rate to 80 percent in the next
two decades from the current 34 percent, it said.  
</P>
