<HEADLINE> India's Election Commissioner on Presidential Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Indian Election Commissioner
G.V.G. Krishnamurty said today that presidential candidate should
be a towering personality with a sound track record and capable of
taking the nation ahead into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
President and vice-president are above politics and not
supposed to be nominees of any political party, he said while
addressing a press conference here.
</P>
<P>
The terms of the current president and vice-president expire on
July 24 and August 20 this year respectively.
</P>
<P>
The election commissioner sought a national debate on issues
relating to the coming presidential and vice-presidential
elections.
</P>
<P>
He said that these issues would have to be considered in-depth
by every section of the society as the persons going to occupy
these two high offices would be symbolizing the trust of the
nation.
</P>
<P>
The tradition of any political party claiming to have its own
president must go, he said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with India's constitution, president and
vice-president are not elected directly but by members of the
electoral college including all the MPs both in parliament and
state assemblies in the country.  
</P>
