<HEADLINE> HK Insurance Industry Records Double Digit Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's insurance industry
recorded double digit growth of 12 percent in 1995 although at a
slower pace than the previous year, an official release said
today.
</P>
<P>
The release said total gross premiums in respect of general
business and long term business in 1995 amounted to 43.8 billion
HK dollars (5.62 billion US dollars), representing some four
percent of Hong Kong's gross domestic product for that year.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the industry said the growth was contributed
mainly by the growth in long term business.
</P>
<P>
Property damage business continued to be the largest
contributor to general business gross premiums, accounting for
about 30 percent of the total. This was followed by general
liability business with a market share of 20 percent, and motor
vehicle business with a market share of 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
The relatively substantial growth of long term business was
mainly the result of the continuous expansion in individual life
business.
</P>
<P>
Currently there are 221 authorized insurers operating in Hong
Kong. 
</P>
