During the summit between Presidents Bill Clinton and Boris
Yeltsin, Russia accepted NATO's eastward expansion in principle
and the talks helped continue, expand and deepen the dialogue
between NATO and Russia, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Gabor
Szentivanyi told the press.
