<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Austrian National Council Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with a delegation from the Austrian National Council led by its
president Heinz Fischer here today, saying that China will join
efforts with Austria to develop a long-term, stable bilateral
relationship facing the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China and Austria are two friendly nations
without any direct conflicts of interest but strong economic
complementarity. The two countries have broad prospects of
developing long-term and stable friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the past few years, friendly cooperation
between the two countries has been continuously expanding and that
leaders of the two sides have kept constant contacts with each
other. This has created favorable conditions for the overall
development of bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that further enhancement of Sino-Austrian cooperation
in all fields will be in the interest of not only the two peoples,
but also peace and stability in the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that disputes between countries can be solved and
bilateral relations be improved through friendly negotiation on
the basis of good will and seeking common ground and putting aside
differences. The exchange of visits and friendly dialogues can
deepen understanding, expand common ground and diminish
differences even though some problems cannot be solved overnight,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Calling Fischer "an old friend of the Chinese people," Jiang
said that Fischer's visit will have a positive effect on the
all-round development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said that exchange and cooperation between the two
countries in economic, cultural, and other fields have been
growing smoothly. Austria wishes to continue the exchange and
cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Fischer conveyed Austrian President Thomas
Klestil's good wishes to Jiang. Jiang asked Fischer to convey his
regards to Klestil.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee Chen Muhua attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the NPC Standing Committee, the Austrian
delegation arrived in China on Monday. 
</P>
