<HEADLINE> HK To Extend Sex Education to Kindergarten Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Sex education will be extended
to kindergartens and primary schools under proposals in the draft
revised Guidelines on Sex Education in Schools (1997) to be issued
 by the Education Department next month.
</P>
<P>
Julian Leung, assistant director of the Education Department,
said that revisions to the former guidelines are necessary in view
 of the rapid social changes over the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
A working group comprising academics, school heads, teachers
and Education Department officers was formed in early 1996 to
compile the revised guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Leung said that the draft revised guidelines aim at helping
teachers to equip students at all levels, starting from
pre-primary level, with the attitudes, values and knowledge
necessary for resolving sex tensions, communicating, building
relationships, self-esteem and concept, and for making decisions
based on informed choices.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Self-reflection, exploration and clarification of
values are given due weight."
</P>
<P>
The draft revised guidelines also define the roles of
principals, teachers, parents, school social workers, students and
 voluntary agencies in sex education.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is recommended that schools should support a
sex education committee or coordinator to support, promote and
coordinate various activities and make liaison with other
committees such as those on civic education and health education.
</P>
</TEXT>
