<P>
Rong thanked Gore for going to the Chinese embassy in the US to
extend condolences on the death of Deng Xiaoping recently.
</P>
<P>
Rong commented that Deng had made "major, historic"
contributions to the development of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Chinese side is ready to work with the US
side to further advance bilateral relations in commemorating Deng,
a great figure.
</P>
<P>
Gore told Rong that he had looked forward to a meeting with
Rong, who has played a big role in implementing the opening policy
and bringing foreign investment into China.
</P>
<P>
Gore said the US firmly supports China's entry into the World
Trade Organization, adding that China's joining the WTO is in the
interests of China, the US and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
According to Gore, President Jiang Zemin and President Bill
Clinton expressed hope when they met in Manila last November that
the issue (of China's entering the WTO) will be resolved by the
time they have exchanged visits.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that this goal can be achieved as long
as the two sides can reach an agreement of commercial significance.
</P>
<P>
Gore is currently on an official visit to China as a guest of
Chinese Premier Li Peng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
