<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Newspapers Hail 1,000-Day Countdown for Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Leading newspapers in Macao today
hailed the 1,000-day countdown for Macao's return to China, which
is observed today, saying it is a "day filled with exultation."
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong in less than 100 days and Macao in
1,000 days will be days of glory for the two regions," said a
commentary in today's "Macao Daily News." "They will be the
milestones in the reunification of China, and fruit of Deng
Xiaoping's great concept of 'one country, two systems.'"
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that after China resumes its exercise of
sovereignty over Macao, there will be no land in Asia governed by
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Macao has a long-lasting significance, which is
well beyond Macao itself, and beyond the relations between China
and Portugal," it said.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal signed the "Joint Declaration on the
Question of Macao" on April 13, 1987. The joint declaration
subsequently became a guideline for the transition of Macao before
 December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
As the time draws near the 10th anniversary of the signing of
the joint declaration, the commentary said, much efforts are yet
to be made on the three leading issues of Macao's transition --
the localization of civil service and law and the implementation
of the use of Chinese as an official language.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the commentary stressed, the promotion of the
basic law of Macao, which will serve as a mini-constitution for
Macao after 1999, should continue so that every residents in Macao
 will be familiar with the law.
</P>
<P>
It urged all residents of Macao to work hard to help expand
Macao's economy, and create a social environment conducive to a
stable transition and a smooth transfer of power in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the "Va Kio" newspaper said in a commentary that
the return of Macao in 1,000 days means a "reunion after
over-400-year separation," an "end of foreigners' ruling," a
"beginning of Macao people governing Macao" and a "resumption of
national dignity."
</P>
<P>
In addition, the 1,000-day countdown means an urgency,
"demanding us to quicken the process of transition and make the
transition a success."
</P>
<P>
"Although the task remains arduous in the coming 1,000 days,
Macao residents should be confident in their future," said the
commentary. "Macao will see a stable transition, and will have a
bright future in 1,000 days." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
