<HEADLINE> 10 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in operations by the
Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, an official
statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the government troops launched armed attacks
against a group of PKK militants in the areas of Kilibogan and
Gaz Tepe in Hani town of Diyarbakir, center of southeastern
Turkey, under the support of Turkish fighters and armored
helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The 10 PKK rebels were killed by the Turkish security forces
in the clashes in the region, it said, adding that the death toll
of the PKK rebels would rise.
</P>
<P>
The government troops also captured two PKK guerrillas in
Lice town of Diyarbakir province during the operations, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the security forces are continuing their
operations in a bid to wipe out the PKK rebels in the region
where the PKK has been fighting a 12-year-old guerrilla war for
self-rule, which has claimed over 21,000 lives since August
1984. 
</P>
