<HEADLINE> CAF Cancels Afro-Asian Champions' Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- This year's Afro-Asian
Nations Cup competition between Saudi Arabia and South Africa has
been cancelled, the Confederation of African Football (CAF)
announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
CAF said the cancellation was due to a heavy schedule of
qualifying matches for the World Cup and African Nations Cup
finals next year. Both countries will be playing in the
Confederations Cup in Riyadh in December.
</P>
<P>
The Afro-Asian Nations Cup is traditionally played every two
years between the African champions and the winners of the Asian
Cup.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia won the Asian Cup competition in December, 10
months after South Africa chalked up the title in the African
Nations Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The Afro-Asian Nations Cup has run since 1985, with Cameroon,
Algeria, Japan, Nigeria and South Korea winning previous
editions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
