<HEADLINE> Turkish President Demirel Arrives in Dhaka Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
arrived here today on a three-day state visit and he will attend
the state functions of Bangladesh's Independence Day on March 26.
</P>
<P>
A red carpet was rolled out to receive President Demirel at the
Zia International Airport as he flew into Dhaka from Islamabad
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina received the Turkish President, who headed a
127-member entourage including two ministers and 30 businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Expansion of bilateral economic cooperation and exchange of
cultural programs will be the main focus of the official talks
tonight between President Demirel and Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina, according to a Foreign Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will chart out areas to expand the existing
volume of trade. Last year, Dhaka exported 20 million U.S. dollars
worth of goods to Turkey and imported products worth around 35
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Three agreements are also likely to be signed between Dhaka and
Ankara. The accords will be on cultural exchange for three years,
civil aviation protocol for establishing air links and cooperation
in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Demirel and Hasina are also likely to discuss progress of the
"D-8" (Development Eight Islamic Countries) grouping initiated by
Turkey and due to be launched in the June summit of the eight
founding members in Islamabad, the Foreign Ministry official
added.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has invited three heads of state to attend its 25th
anniversary Independence Day function. Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat and South African President Nelson Mandela will
arrive here later today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
