<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to rise
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained 5.55 points to close at 2099.95 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was still thin at 128.92 million units,
worth 291.46 million Singapore dollars (about 205.25 million US
dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 229 to 85, while 293
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
MBF Holdings was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 3.85 million units. It was followed by
Meiban Plastic which had 3.52 million shares traded. BZM SIAF
warrant was next with 3.3 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local property developer City Developments warrant98 led the
gainers of the day as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 10.6
Singapore dollars. Asia Pacific, the Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation (OCBC) Foreign, Robinson, and the Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) gained 30 cents each to close at 7.15, 17.6, 6.35,
12.7 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the CMSPort and the Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign, and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) F A
shared the top spot on the losers' list as each of them declined
by 40 cents to end at 5.1 Hong Kong dollars, 17.5 and 15 Singapore
dollars respectively. Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) fell by 20 cents to
close at 15 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
