<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Portuguese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
here this afternoon with Portuguese Defense Minister Antonio
Vitorino.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting in Zhongnanhai, Jiang, also chairman of the
Central Military Commission, extended welcome to the minister for
his China visit and said that he believed the minister's visit
would promote the growth of friendship and cooperation between the
two countries and their armies.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal have seen smooth development of bilateral
cooperation in the fields of politics, economy, culture,
education, science and technology, and military affairs, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
The president said that frequent high-level exchange of visits
over recent years have played a positive role in pushing forward
the growth of the overall bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China and Portugal have enjoyed sound
cooperation in implementing their joint declaration on the Macao
issue. A series of issues concerning the smooth transition of
Macao have been addressed with the concerted efforts from the two
countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, China is fully confident of the future of
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Vitorino is visiting China at the invitation of Chinese Defense
Minister Chi Haotian, who is also vice-chairman of China's Central
Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Vitorino said that as the first defense minister to visit China
from the European Union nations in the past decade, he is pleased
to have a chance to exchange views with Chinese military leaders.
