<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gore Visits Chinese High School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- US Vice-President Al Gore visited
an experimental high school associated with Beijing Teacher's
University today and learned about the school's program of "Global
Learning and Observations to Benefit the Environment"(GLOBE).
</P>
<P>
The Globe program, initiated by Gore on April 22, 1994, or the
World Earth Day, is an international cooperative project on
environmental education.
</P>
<P>
The experimental high school, together with three other Chinese
schools, joined in the program in 1996 after China and the US
signed a cooperative agreement on the project.
</P>
<P>
At an outdoor observation station of the school, Gore and
several senior students gauged the temperature, the rainfall and
other environmental conditions, then stored the data on a
computer. After processing, the computer presented an image that
showed the students the environmental conditions they live in.
</P>
<P>
After learning that all the students of the class have
participated in the Globe program and collect such information
every day, Gore exclaimed, "Very impressive!"
</P>
<P>
The students presented Gore with a plate bearing a Peking Opera
painted face. Gore accepted the gift with pleasure and told the
students he will put the plate in a place of honor at his official
residence.
</P>
<P>
Invited by the students to write in the school's guest-book,
Gore penned, "Congratulations on your success with the Globe
Program."
</P>
<P>
The Vice-President and his party also toured the Palace Museum
this afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
