<HEADLINE> Annan to Leave Angola After Meeting Angolan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
is to end his four-day visit to Angola today after meeting with
Angolan President Eduardo dos Santos last night on the lastest
development in the country's peace process.
</P>
<P>
Annan told Dos Santos that Jonas Savimbi, the leader of the
opposition National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA), promised in central Bailundo earlier on Monday that all
UNITA lawmakers will arrive in capital Luanda today.
</P>
<P>
With the arrival of UNITA lawmakers and politicians, things
will be ready for consultation between the Angolan government and
UNITA on the date of the inauguration of the government of
national unity and reconciliation, said Santos.
</P>
<P>
Some certain procedures will be carried out so as to ensure
the UNITA parliamentary members to assume office legally, he
added.
</P>
<P>
However, said Santos, it is not suitable at the time for
himself and Savimbi to meet each other although he has repeated
his invitation to Savimbi times again.
</P>
<P>
His invitation to Savimbi for face-to-face talks is still
effective, Santos said.
</P>
<P>
Annan, who arrived on Saturday, will leave here today for
Togo's capital Lome to attend a summit of the Organization of
African Unity on the Zairean crisis. 
</P>
