<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Mekong River Reaps Good Rice Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Mekong River Delta, the biggest
rice producer in Vietnam, is expected to harvest about 9 million
tonnes of winter-spring rice crop.
</P>
<P>
The total area under rice cultivation in the delta is 210,000
hectares with an average yield of about 6.5 to 7 tonnes per
hectare.
</P>
<P>
A local press report said today that Vietnam's Prime Minister
Vo Van Kiet has asked government sectors, including all commercial
banks, to support traders in buying rice in time and at prices in
favor of local rice growers.
</P>
<P>
He said rice trading must benefit rice growers while
maintaining national food security and boosting export.
</P>
<P>
he confirmed at a conference in Ho Chi Minh City that the
export target for the year is 2.7 million tonnes.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the government has instructed departments
concerned immediately to undertake flood control projects and get
prepared for this year's flooding season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
