<HEADLINE> China Has No Plan of Economic Cooperation and Trade with Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- China has no Plan of having
economic cooperation and trade with Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Cui Tiankai said this in
response to a reporter's question at a routine press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
Cui said that reports alleging that an individual Chinese
company had signed a contract with Iraq on food and aid for oil
were totally groundless.
</P>
<P>
China has always strictly abided by all the UN resolutions
regarding Iraq, and has no plan of having economic cooperation and
trade with Iraq at a time when sanctions against Iraq are not
lifted, added Cui. 
