<HEADLINE> Rare Dugongs Appear in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 25 (xinhua) -- Several dugongs have been seen in a
national park of Vietnam's Con Dao island, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
A local fisherman caught a 2.5-metre-long dugong weighing about
200 kg early this month and a 3-metre-long dead dugong was found
in this area.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that there are between 8-12 dugongs in the
park's area, according to an expert from the national park.
</P>
<P>
Dugongs are a rare and endangered animal species in need of
protection. They are mostly found in the Philippine
islands. 
</P>
