major topics to be discussed will be the Caspian Sea oil issue.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has put forward a proposal of transporting the Caspian
Sea oil along the planned Baku-Ceyhan (southern Turkey) route to
the world markets but this tentative idea has not been approved
by Azerbaijan so far.
</P>
<P>
Press reports said the proposal which will make considerable
profits for Turkey has already been ignored or even turned down by
Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
A senior Turkish Foreign Ministry official, who asked not to
be named, denied such reports, saying the Azerbaijani side has
expressed support for the construction of the route and the route
would be probably marked in the joint declaration to be signed at
the end of Aliyev's visit. 
