<HEADLINE> Zaireans Overrun Zairean Embassy in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Zairean residents in Uganda
overran their embassy in Kampala, capital of Uganda for 40
minutes on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mass media here reported today that over 50 young men rushed
into the embassy, burnt the Zairean flag and Zairean President
Mobutu Sese Seko's portrait and hoisted the deep blue, striped
red, yellow, red and gold star flag of the Alliance for
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo/Zaire (ADFL).
</P>
<P>
Charge d'Affairs Bwana Muzuri Kanungu and other embassy staff
were paraded in front of the embassy building to witness the act.
</P>
<P>
leader of the Zairean residents walumba mbuliyenda on behalf
of 300 Ugandans in the country was quoted as saying, ''we have
not been violent because we supporters of democracy cherish peace
for all.''
</P>
<P>
he said, ''we have stormed the place because this building
belongs to us and not the dictator in Kimshasa.''
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Foreign Ministry spokesman Louis Balinda considered
the act as illegal, saying police should step in.
</P>
<P>
Last evening, police were deployed here to control the riot
and guard the embassy property.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that last week Zairean residents in Paris,
France, numbering about 50 briefly occupied the embassy there.
</P>
</TEXT>
