<HEADLINE> Kenya Launches Export Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Association of
Manufacturers (KAM) has started the Export Development Support
Project to help local firms improve the quality of their
products.
</P>
<P>
At a on-going workshop attended by 48 companies, KAM Executive
Officer S.N. Thiga said on Monday that the project would focus on
implementing quality controls and waste disposal especially with
regard to food safety.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the project would also provide assistance to
companies in improving packaging and designs in order to enhance
their competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The KAM will undertake market trials in specialized
exhibitions to widen products exposure for the local companies,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The association will ensure financing for the expansion of
firms to meet the requirements of targeted markets, Thiga said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the assistance provided by his association
would be restricted to privately owned companies and detailed
quality criteria for assistance would be worked out next month.
</P>
