<HEADLINE> Bank Chooses Loan Priorities in Agricultural Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
will target certain groups to receive loans in the agricultural
sector this year.
</P>
<P>
According to an official from the Bank, the quality of
agricultural produce and pillar industries will determine
priorities of loans offered by the Bank this year.
</P>
<P>
He said that the construction of agricultural bases with
certain characteristics, such as the cash crop bases in the
northeast provinces, the quality cotton base in northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, and the tropical agricultural
products base in south China's Hainan province, will rerceive
special support from the Bank.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he noted, the Bank will select a number of
well-operated agricultural enterprises to promote the integration
of their production, processing and sales.
</P>
<P>
According to him, preferences will also be given to
agriculture-related industries such as fertilizer, pesticides, and
farm machinery in providing loans.  
