is an "important event" in Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Chinese side is "ready work with the US side
to advance bilateral relations."
</P>
<P>
Gore, who toured the Palace Museum right before his meeting
with Rong, described the tour as an "impressive experience."
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met with Gore. Zhu said he
believes the visit will play an important role in enhancing the
friendship between the two peoples and the friendly relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Learning that Gore is to deliver a speech at Qinghua University
Wednesday, Zhu said it is a "marvellous" arrangement since the
university is one of China's foremost institutions of higher
learning and also his Alma Mater.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed Gore on the progress of China's economic
construction since the implementation of reform and open
policy. Gore praised Zhu for making remarkable contributions to
China's economic achievements.
</P>
<P>
Gore, who arrived here Monday on an official visit, will also
meet Vice-Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress Tian Jiyun later this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
This morning, Chinese Premier Li Peng and Gore held talks,
exchanging views on bilateral relations and other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Following their talks, the two leaders attended and addressed a
Sino-US forum on environment and development. 
