<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Accuses Israel of Challenging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today accused
Israel of challenging all international resolutions which ban it
from changing the nature of the occupied Arab territories.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Information Minister Fuad Faresi quoted Saudi King Fahd
as saying after Monday night's cabinet session that Israel must
stop all its expansionist actions, the establishment of new
settlements on occupied Palestinian territories and its
aggressive practices against the Palestinian people, according
to Kuwait News Agency reports from the Saudi capital of Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi king said Saudi Arabia was extremely alarmed at the
repeated Israeli violations of Jerusalem's holy places.
</P>
<P>
King Fahd reaffirmed his country's support for the realization
of comprehensive, just and permanent peace in the region. But he
stressed that this could not be achieved unless the Palestinian
people obtain all their legitimate rights and able to establish
their independent state and retrieve Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The king said his country was satisfied with the results of
the extraordinary conference of the Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC) held on March 22-23 in Islamabad, Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The special OIC summit in a statement declared Jerusalem an
integral part of Palestine and asserted support for the
Palestinians in their talks with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The declaration from the 54-member organization followed a
series of speeches by Arab and other Muslim delegates slamming
Israel's decision to start work on a new settlement in East
Jerusalem. 
</P>
