<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Suspends Imports of Pork From Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Singapore decided today to
suspend the imports of pork and pork products from Taiwan in view
of the outbreak of the foot and mouth disease there.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Primary Production Department (PPD) said that
only a small quantity of pork was imported from Taiwan as
Singapore's main source of pork supply was Malaysia and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
All pork imports from Taiwan are suspended with immediate
effect, the PPD said.
</P>
<P>
Amid growing public fears over a major outbreak of the highly
contagious foot-and-mouth disease among pigs in Taiwan, the
slaughter of more than 100,000 hogs at the infected farms had been
ordered.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
