<HEADLINE> Memorial Temple for Minister from 2,500 Years Ago To be Renovated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A memorial temple for a minister of
the Chu State in the Spring and Autumn period (770-476 BC) will be
renovated in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
Minister Sun Shu'ao was in charge of building the Anfengtang
Dam, one of the four greatest water conservancy projects in
ancient China.
</P>
<P>
The dam, now under state protection, is still in use today. The
temple alongside the dam, however, suffered serious damage over
the past millenium.
</P>
<P>
Renovation of the temple, including a display hall featuring
the history of the dam, is expected to be completed by the end of
the year. 
</P>
