<HEADLINE> Hebei Optimizes Export Commodity Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- To optimize its export
commodity structure, north China's Hebei Province has improved its
commodity quality, and diversified its markets and foreign trade
strategy.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial government has said that Hebei
will increase the export quota of mechanical and electrical
equipment in 1997, making it account for 15 percent of the
province's total exports.
</P>
<P>
A major force in foreign trade, the export quota of
overseas-backed enterprises covered 20 percent of the total export
in 1996. This year, Hebei will combine its practice of attracting
overseas investment with expanding export.
</P>
<P>
Customs statistics show that Hebei imported two billion US
dollars-worth of commodities in 1996. The province has carried out
a foreign trade strategy of using imports to strengthen
exports. Centering on import, economic development and export, the
province has increased export scale and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Hebei will reorganize its structure of export-oriented
enterprises and carry out import and export agent systems in
1997. 
