<HEADLINE> Romania to Stabilize Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Romania will stabilize the
exchange rate between the Romanian currency, the leu and the
U.S. dollar, at the rate of one dollar to 7,000-7,500 lei.
</P>
<P>
The director of the Romanian National Central Bank, Mugur
Isarescu, said on Sunday that the revaluation of the leu was not
conducive to the country's exports.
</P>
<P>
The market quotation of foreign exchange in Romanian state
banks was one dollar to 7,011 lei today, but it was one dollar to
6,900 lei in exchange markets, the director said.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months of this year, the exchange rate between
the leu and U.S. dollar slumped from one dollar to 4,100 lei at
the beginning of 1997, to one dollar to 9,000 lei in February,
causing price hikes.
</P>
<P>
In early March, banks in Romania raised the interest rate of
the leu and the rate of exchange in cash between the leu and
dollar, attracting a large amount of leu deposits.
</P>
<P>
This month, Romanian national banks purchased near 100 million
dollars from foreign exchange markets, stopping the further leu
devaluation.
</P>
<P>
Isarescu said foreign currency trade was not allowed in
Romania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
