<HEADLINE> 121 Vietnamese Migrants in Hong Kong Sent Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A group of 121 Vietnamese
migrants (VMs) returned by air to Hanoi, Vietnam, today on the
98th flight under the Orderly Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
The majority of the returnees, comprising 78 men, 17 women, 15
boys and 11 girls, are from the northern part of Vietnam. 55 of
the returnees are from the central and southern parts of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Most of the returnees arrived in Hong Kong in 1989, 1991 and
1996, with the remaining in 1988, 1990 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
The group brought to 9,923 the total number repatriated on ORP
flights since November 1991. 
