<HEADLINE> HK Convention-Exhibition Center Wins World Prizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center (HK Center) recently won two major international
prizes for its outstanding services with trade promotion.
</P>
<P>
The fourth quarter issue of "Meetings And Incentive Travel", an
influential periodical in Britain, conferred the HK Center a prize
as the best center for conventions and exhibition in the world.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the HK Center was also awarded a prize titled as
"CIM Honor
Prize" by a noted Australian magazine "Convention and Incentive
Marketing (CIM)".
</P>
<P>
The two prizes have shown that the HK Center has been
prestigious in Europe and Australia and with the completion of the
extended section of the HK Center, it will be the first-class
convention and exhibition center in the world.
</P>
<P>
An official of the HK Center said that in 1996, the center has
hosted 1,940 programs including 110 large-sized exhibitions, 70
large-sized conferences and more than 1,700 business functions.
</P>
<P>
The HK Center has been selected as the venue for Hong Kong's
handover ceremony on June 30 as well as for the 52nd Annual
Meetings of the World Bank Group and the International Monetary
Fund in September.  
</P>
