<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Central Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.3 on
the open-end Richter scale rocked central Chile, including its
capital city of Santiago, late today.
</P>
<P>
Authorities said there were report of injuries or damage.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, which lasted 45 seconds, sent residents in Santiago
rushing out of their houses when it struck at 9:14 p.m. local time
(0015 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located about 80 kilometers beneath the
center of Santiago, according to the Chilean National Emergency
Office.
</P>
<P>
Santiago was last struck by a major tremor in March 1985, which
caused deaths and serious damage to buildings in the older parts
of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
