<DOCNO> XIE19970325.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Pooling Funds for Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Pudong New Area in Shanghai,
China's largest financial and economic center, has become a
reservoir of cash flow from home and abroad, where Chinese
government could only afford a minor part of the total investment
for its development.
</P>
<P>
Official sources say that a total of 200 billion yuan has been
pumped into Pudong New Area during the Eighth Five-Year Plan
period (1991-1995), of which government investment accounted for
less than 44 percent, peaking at 87.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investors from home and abroad have provided most of the cash
needed for fixed assets investment in Pudong New Area over the
past few years, the sources said, adding that a total of 12
billion US dollars of overseas investment in contractual value
has been lured.
</P>
<P>
Pudong New Area has always continued to promote to overseas
investors its rare business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The same attention has also been given by Pudong New Area to
upgrade its investment environment, and to increase the return
rate of investment.
</P>
<P>
So far, these efforts have started to pay back in Pudong, which
has seen a quick growth of overseas investment in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has built two giant bridges over, and a tunnel under the
Huangpu River, and an efficient road network, over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 100 office buildings have been built in
Pudong, and 8,000 foreign-funded and Chinese enterprises, put into
production.
</P>
<P>
Some well-known overseas multinationals and banks have moved
their headquarters or headquarters in China to Pudong in recent
years, which also brought in a large amount of investment.
</P>
<P>
It is said that Pudong will need a total of 330 billion yuan in
investment in fixed assets during the 1996-2000 period, most of
which will also be funded by home and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
About one third of the investment needed will be injected in
the massive construction of infrastructure projects, the sources
point out.
</P>
<P>
Construction of an international airport in Pudong, a subway
under the Huangpu River, and other major infrastructure projects
now is well underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
