<HEADLINE> Citic to Become Global Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- China International Trust and
Investment Corp. (Citic), a major investment arm of the State
Council, is seeking to become a global giant by the year 2000,
today's "China Daily" quoted a Citic official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1979 by Rong Yiren, who is now China's
Vice-president, Citic earned 2.47 billion yuan in profits last
year, a 21 percent rise from the previous year. Its assets value
exceeded 191 billion yuan by the end of last year, a nearly 15
percent rise over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Citic made a breakthrough last year by launching a securities
company in January, doing businesses in the fields of securities
trading brokerage, underwriting stock issues, fund management and
financial consulting.
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in Beijing, Citic today is one of the country's
largest investment companies, with its investment involved in
banking, nonferrous metals, machinery, automobiles, real estate
and service industries. 
</P>
