safeguard the security of Albania, where more than 100 people have
been killed in armed unrest throughout the country over the past
weeks.
</P>
<P>
Oymen is the first high-ranking Turkish official to visit
Albania since violence erupted in this Balkan country over the
collapse of investment schemes that had bankrupted thousands of
families.
