<HEADLINE> Chilean President Emphasizes Value of Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
today called for reforms in the country's educational sector,
which he deemed as the basis for national development.
</P>
<P>
After inaugurating the last section of a highway linking the
cities of Cauquenes and Quirihue, the Chilean president said
education offered the only opportunity for integral development.
</P>
<P>
Unless the Chileans have access to high quality education, Frei
said, they "will always remain underdeveloped".
</P>
<P>
Chile's modernization obliges the country to make progress in
all walks of life, and to strengthen its institutions as well as
the economy and society. 
