<HEADLINE> Diver Fu Tops Best of Best Athletes in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Diver Fu Mingxia won her first
and greatest honour by topping the 10 best Chinese athletes who
were honored here Monday night.
</P>
<P>
In the 18th edition of the annual gala, Fu Mingxia, 18,
received the biggest number of 261,242, a clear sweep of all the
votes casted by the sports fans all around the country.
</P>
<P>
The woman teenager diver from Hubei province, had the national
anthem echoed twice at the Atlanta Olympics, becoming the first
diver in 36 years winning two gold medals at the same game.
</P>
<P>
"It was my first time to be selected into the best 10 athletes,
and surely it was a great honour for me," said Fu with a toothy
smile.
</P>
<P>
Ranked second in the votings was woman paddler Deng Yaping with
260,306 votes, a reward for her successful defense of two titles
in the Olympics, a historical feat never attained by any of her
predecessors.
</P>
<P>
Liu Guoliang who also won two titles in the Atlanta men's table
tennis tournaments, became the third-placer with 258,028 votes.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiaoshuang, the first Chinese gymnast winning the all-around
Olympic title, received 257,068 votes, beating woman runner Wang
Junxia to the fifth spot on 255,379.
</P>
<P>
Wang, 24, clocked 14:59.88 to take the women's 5,000 meters,
the first Olympic gold medal for the Chinese women runners, before
awarding China one more silver medal in the 10,000 race.
</P>
<P>
The bottom half of the best 10 were woman swimmer Le Jingyi,
Olympic champion of the 100m freestyle, strongman Zhan Xugang,
world record holder in the men's 70-kg category, men's springboard
Olympic champion Xiong Ni, Judoka Sun Fuming who won the first
gold medal for China in Atlanta and woman shooter Li Duihong,
winner of the 25m pistol in Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
