<HEADLINE> Chile Reports Trade Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Chile reported a trade surplus
of 139 million U.S. dollars in February and a total of 173 million
dollars for the first two months this year, the central bank said
today.
</P>
<P>
The February trade surplus was the result of 1.32 billion
dollars worth of exports versus 1.18 billion dollars worth of
imports, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Exports grew last month due to a 3.4-percent rise in overseas
copper sales, despite a price drop of the metal and lower
quotations of other products.
</P>
<P>
Chile's net international reserves reached 16.423 billion
dollars in the first two weeks of March after an increase of 125
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
