<HEADLINE> Chile Auto Production Up 16.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Chile's automobile production
reached 2,600 units during the first two months of this year, an
increase of 16.5 percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Corporation de Fomento de la Production said today that of
the total number of vehicles assembled, 1,857 were small trucks
and 734 were cars.
</P>
<P>
It said 1,643 units were produced in February, of which 1,160
were assembled by the General Motors Chile, S.A.
</P>
<P>
The automobile production of this company rose to 1,857 units
during the first two months of this year, while a total of 1,686
were turned out in the same period last year. 
