<HEADLINE> Ukraine Lauds Clinton-Yeltsin Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine welcomed the Helsinki summit
between United States President Bill Clinton and his Russian
counterpart, Boris Yeltsin, on the eastward expansion of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian News Agency reported Monday that Ukraine agreed
to the Helsinki declaration which aims to build a common, secure,
integrated and inseparable Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Ukraine Foreign Ministry said:``The declaration expressed
(the premise) that no organization alone can provide Europe with
security.''
</P>
<P>
The statement praised Russia and the U.S. for respecting
sovereignty and territorial integrity of concerned
nations. ``Every country has undeniable rights to choose means of
protecting its security.''
</P>
<P>
It also expressed regret that Clinton and Yeltsin failed to
resolve differences over NATO's expansion.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the document to be drafted by NATO and Russia
could reinforce European security and the basic benefits of all
related nations. 
</P>
