<HEADLINE> Match-Rigging Retrial Set in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The retrial of former Liverpool
goalie Bruce Grobbelaar and two other footers on match-rigging
charges will begin on June 4 this year, a judge ruled on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Together with former Wimbledon goalie Hans Segers, former Aston
Villa striker John Fashanu and Malaysian businessman Heng Suan
Lim, Grobbelaar is charged of rigging soccer matches on behalf of
an Asian betting syndicate in Britain's premier league.
</P>
<P>
The previous trial concluded on March 4 after eight weeks with
no verdict. The retrial will also be held in Winchester.
</P>
<P>
Grobbelaar faced a separate charge of accepting money as an
inducement to throw matches.
</P>
<P>
John Fashanu and Malaysian businessman Lim were charged with
acting as middlemen in the alleged conspiracy. All four denied
the charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
