<DOCNO> XIE19970325.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador in Arrears With Paris Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador is in arrears with 380
million U.S. dollars of capital and interest payments to the Paris
Club, official statements say.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran government recently began talks in Spain with the
creditor governments to discuss re-financing the
380-million-dollar overdue payments. These amount to almost
one-quarter of the total amount of money Ecuador owes the Paris
Club.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's economic authorities also held talks with the
directors of the International Monetary Fund who are attending the
Inter-American Development Bank meetings.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's foreign debt amounts to about 12.3 billion dollars,
according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
The Paris Club, also known as the Group-10, which includes the
United States, Britain, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, the
Netherlands, Canada, Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland and Luxembourg,
aims to rearrange debt issues between developing nations and
western creditor nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
