<HEADLINE> More Than One Ton of Cocaine Seized in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian authorities seized
more than one ton of cocaine and arrested 11 people connected with
the Cali drug cartel in Colombia, police sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The drugs, totaling 1,339 kilograms and worth an estimated 3.6
million U.S. dollars, were seized after several months of
investigation including police raids and other operations in the
sectors of La Chorrera, San Carlos and Tocumen, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Some 40,000 dollars in bills were confiscated during the police
actions, police said.
</P>
<P>
The first lot of drugs were confiscated when police agents
intercepted a vehicle at a checkpoint in La Chorrera, about 30
kilometers east of the Panamanian capital.
</P>
<P>
An inspection of the vehicle revealed 28 tins of preserved food
that were full of cocaine, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Authorities seized 341 kilograms of cocaine during a second
operation at a residence in San Carlos district, about 90
kilometers north of Panama City, while another 998 kilograms of
the drug were found aboard a vehicle during a third operation.
</P>
</TEXT>
