<HEADLINE> Chile Meeting to Discuss Pacific Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The 12th council meeting of the
Pacific Economic Cooperation will be held in Chile this September,
according to Edgardo Boeninger, president of the council and the
Chilean Pacific Foundation.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for Latin America to host the annual
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Boeninger said that more than 1,000 government officials,
businessmen and scholars will attend the meeting of the council
which is comprised of 22 countries and regions from along the
Pacific rim.
</P>
<P>
Matters of common interest will be discussed.
</P>
<P>
Boeninger has recently visited Argentina, Brazil, Peru,
Colombia and Mexico to coordinate the participation of the meeting
by Latin American countries. He received support and commitment
from those countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
