<HEADLINE> Czech Tichy Win US Alpine Skiing Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Martin Tichy of the Czech
Republic came from seventh place after the first run to take the
men's slalom in the US Alpine Championships in Caarrabassett
Valley, Maine on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tichy, a member of the Czech national team who lives in
Vancouver, took the title in a combined time of 1:36.47.
</P>
<P>
Uros Pavlovcic of Slovenia, who goes to school at Sierra Nevada
College, tied for second with local favorite Casey Puckett in
1:36.70.
</P>
<P>
Kristina Koznick, 21, posted the best time for each run in the
women's race to win the title for the third straight year.
</P>
<P>
She finished in 1 minute 30.05 seconds, with 1.63 seconds ahead
of Carrie Sheinberg. 
</P>
