<HEADLINE> Eriksson Grabs Lead in Portugese Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Swede Kenneth Eriksson geared up
his Sabaru Impreza to grab the lead of the Portugese Rally with a
14-second margin in Povoa De Varzim on Monday.
</P>
<P>
World champion Tommi Makinen of Finland, in a Mitsubishi
Lancer, finished second, ahead of Freddy Loix of Belgium who was a
distant 1:15 away from Eriksson.
</P>
<P>
The rally was reeled off on Sunday, yet the first special stage
of the day was declared void by the organizers after Makinen's
brakes were damaged which cornered him to finish in 63rd spot.
</P>
<P>
After the first day of the three-day event, Eriksson clocked
first in one hour 58 minutes and 54 seconds through 12 stages
which covered a distance of 168.7 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Both Colin McRae of Scotland and Carlos Sainz of Spain were
forced out of the tough race due to mechanical problems.
</P>
<P>
McRae, leader of the world championship standings, withdrew
with brake problems on his Subaru Impreza while Sainz, second in
the championship, was forced out by his Ford Escort's faulty
gearbox.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese Rally is the fourth event of the world
championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
