<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Says He Might Leave Barcelona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 24 (Xinhua) -- World player of the year Ronaldo
said on Monday the "door is open" for him to leave Barcelona at
the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian striker said he felt he had a right to negotiate
with other clubs because club president Jose Luis Nunez had not
kept an agreement to improve his contract.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona, inspired by his breath-taking displays, had
indicated to open negotiations over a new contract, which would in
theory have raised Ronaldo's price to at least four billion
pesetas (27.8 million US dollars) and his annual pay cheque from
an estimated 200 million pesetas (1.39 million US dollars) to 500
million (3.47 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, Barcelona now say no new deal will be reached before
the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
The young Brazilian was signed from Dutch side PSV Eindhoven in
the close season for a then world-record fee of 2.5 billion
pesetas (17.4 million US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
