<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Meet Togo's President on Eve of OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahamed Salim said here
today he hopes the Wednesday OAU summit on the Zaire crisis will
make decisions for the unity and territorial integrity of Zaire.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in a statement issued here today after
meeting President of Togo Gnassingbe Eyadema.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief said that the summit is aimed at making the
Zairean people reach understanding among themselves to end their
hostilities.
</P>
<P>
The summit is a very important meeting which many African
countries will attend, especially 17 members of the OAU Central
Organ for the Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management and
Resolution, to address the problem within the continent.
</P>
<P>
Salim said that he hopes Zairean rebel leader Laurent Kabila
will turn up at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
This will provide a chance for African leaders to make the two
warring sides closer to each other, he added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that "the territorial integrity, national sovereignty,
unity of Zaire is what the OAU supports." 
</P>
