<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zairean Rebel Delegation Arrives at Lome for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A two-member rebel delegation of
Zaire arrived here today for the Wednesday summit of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) aimed to seek a peaceful
solution to the Zaire crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to a local radio tonight, this is the first formal
presence of the Zairean rebels at such an international meeting
on the situation in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The two rebel delegates are Bizima Kahaha and Gaetan Kakudji,
both responsible for foreign affairs in the rebel camp led by
Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
"This is a very important development for creating an
environment for a negotiated settlement, negotiations and
cessation of hostilities," Mohamed Sahnoun, the joint special
envoy of the U.N. and OAU, told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
He said the Zairean governmental delegates will also attend
the summit, but it was not clear whether Zairean President Mobutu
Sese Seko will come or not.
</P>
<P>
When asked if the summit will produce any positive results,
Sahnoun said that "it certainly constitutes a strong pressure for
a peaceful solution" to the Zairean conflict.
</P>
<P>
"We hope this very important development and pressure will
produce some progress toward this solution," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun said that the Nairobi Summit III, to be held on
Tuesday evening and chaired by Kenyan President Denial arap Moi,
will also focus on the situation on Zaire.
</P>
<P>
At the brief summit as a complementary to the OAU summit, Moi
will brief regional leaders on March 19 Nairobi mini-summit which
called for negotiations and an ceasefire in Zaire, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
