<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Attaches Importance to Relations with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- British Deputy Prime Minister
Michael Heseltine said here today Britain attaches importance to
developing good relations with China.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with General Fu Quanyou, member of China's Central
Military Commission and Chief of General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, Heseltine said a smooth hand-over of Hong
Kong to China was a great event and the task of transfer seems
much easier to accomplish now than before as a result of strenuous
efforts jointly made by Britain and China.
</P>
<P>
Britain had good relations with China, he said, adding his
country was the largest European investor in China with improved
bilateral cooperation in the economic field.
</P>
<P>
General Fu, who arrived here Saturday on a five-day official
visit, said it is a world event that China resumes its excercise
of sovereignty over Hong Kong and China hopes the remaining issues
concerning the smooth transfer of power can be resolved properly
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also said his current visit to Britain was aimed at
enhancing understanding, developing friendship and promoting
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Britain is the last leg of General Fu's current four-nation
European visit which has already taken him to Belgium, France and
Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
